Name: insulinoma
Definition: A pancreatic cystadenoma that is characterized by the overproduction of insulin.

Name: pancreatic serous cystadenoma
Definition: A lung cancer that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

Name: microcystic adenoma
Definition: A pancreatic cystadenoma that is characterized by innumerable small cysts lined by bland clear cells.

Name: obsolete atypical adenoma
Definition: A pancreatic cystadenoma that is characterized by innumerable small cysts lined by bland clear cells.

Name: pancreatic mucinous cystadenoma
Definition: A central nervous system adult germ cell tumor that develops from mismigrational pluripotent embryonic cells that remain in the brain after birth

Name: pancreatic colloid cystadenoma
Definition: An adolescence-adult electroclinical syndrome starting in adolescence exhibiting generalized tonic-clonic seizures as the only seizure type.
